article.headline: Indiana St. 79, Murray St. 62
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Harry Marshall scored 16 points to lead Indiana State to a 79-62 win over Murray State Saturday night. The Sycamores (14-13) fell behind 27-10 early but went on a 31-9 run to end the game. Jay Tunnell scored 15 points for the Sycamores and Aaron Carter added 14 off the bench. The Racers (16-11) were led by Bruce Carter's 21 points and five rebounds. Danero Thomas scored the Racers' first 10 points and he finished with 17. Indiana State scored 21 points off 14 Murray State turnovers.
